title: Square Root
text:
In this problem you have to find the Square Root for given number. You may assume that such 
a number exist and it will be always an integer.Solutions to this problem can be submitted in C, C++, Pascal, Algol, Fortran, Ada, Ocaml, Prolog, Whitespace, Brainf**k and Intercal only.Inputt- the number of test cases [t <= 50]thentpositive numbers follow, each of them have up to 800 digits in decimal 
representation.OutputOutput must contain exactly t numbers equal to the square root for given numbers. See sample input/output for details.ExampleInput:3
36
81
226576Output:6
9
476
